## 🛠️ The Minimalist Web Framework

Express is the most popular framework for Node.js. It simplifies routing and handling requests through a concept called **Middleware**.

---

## 1️⃣ Middleware: The Assembly Line

A request in Express is like a product on a conveyor belt. It passes through several functions (middleware) before the response is sent.

```javascript
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log("Logging request...");
  next(); // Pass to the next function
});
```

---

## 2️⃣ Routing & Parameters

Express makes it easy to handle specific URLs and methods.

```javascript
app.get('/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id;
  res.json({ userId: id });
});
```

---

## 3️⃣ Error Handling: The Last Stop

Instead of putting `try/catch` in every route, we use **Centralized Error Middleware** to catch everything in one place.

```javascript
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  res.status(500).send("Something broke!");
});
```

---

## 💡 Professional Tip
Always use `express.json()` middleware at the top of your app to automatically parse JSON data in the request body.
